STM32CubeH7
###########

Origin:
   ST Microelectronics
   http://www.st.com/en/embedded-software/stm32cubeh7.html

Status:
   version v1.13.0

Purpose:
   ST Microelectronics official MCU package for STM32H7 series.

Description:
   This package is an extract of official STM32CubeH7 package written by ST Microelectronics.
   It is composed of STM32Cube hardware abstraction layer (HAL) and low layer (LL) plus a set
   of CMSIS headers files, one for each SoC in STM32H7 series.

Dependencies:
    None.

URL:
   https://github.com/STMicroelectronics/STM32CubeH7

Commit:
   5abb9764b32e11a6557b90bf39531528019b5761

Maintained-by:
   External

License:
   BSD-3-Clause

License Link:
   https://opensource.org/licenses/BSD-3-Clause

Patch List:
   *Changes from official delivery:
    -dos2unix applied
    -trailing white spaces removed

   *Provision to enable hal & ll asserts added
    -Added stm32cube/stm32h7xx/drivers/include/stm32_assert.h
    -Removed unused stm32cube/stm32h7xx/drivers/include/stm32_assert_template.h

   *Fix SDIO initialization failure when skipping card identification sequence
     Fixes an issue in the STM32H7 SDIO driver where HAL_SDIO_Init() fails if
     the card identification sequence is skipped.
     Impacted files:
      stm32cube/stm32h7xx/drivers/src/stm32h7xx_hal_sdio.c

   *Fix HAL_DFSDM_IRQHandler
      HAL_DFSDM_IRQHandler handles IRQ flags in an if {} else if {} condition.
      This causes interrupts to be handled once and only the first flag
      encountered in the condition, while there can be several flags raised.
     Impacted files:
       drivers/src/stm32f7xx_hal_dfsdm.c
     ST Internal Reference: HAL1-27454

   *Define new LL APIs for VREFBUF that will be part of the HAL next release.
      Modifications applied from stm32h7xx-hal-driver repository:
      https://github.com/STMicroelectronics/stm32h7xx-hal-driver/commit/13dbe01ff0be6a24e47d0b4d8cf4de3f22c754a
     - Impacted file: drivers/include/stm32h7xx_ll_system.h
     - See also: https://github.com/zephyrproject-rtos/hal_stm32/pull/381

   *Fix CCM partial-word output handling from next HAL release
     Fixes CCM partial-word output handling for Non-Multiple of 4 Byte Payloads.
     Fix applied from stm32h7xx-hal-driver repository:
     https://github.com/STMicroelectronics/stm32h7xx-hal-driver/commit/cd566efa4e52854f5780e9c022a12af5bda1ad78
     - Impacted file: drivers/src/stm32h7xx_hal_cryp.c
     - See also: https://github.com/zephyrproject-rtos/hal_stm32/pull/380
     - ST Internal Reference: 226589

   See release_note.html from STM32Cube
